Yangman, "seeding" is where you leave your Torrent client running, so that others may get parts of the torrent from you, the same way you got your copy from still others. In short, you "give back" for leeching (or "taking").  It generally costs nothing other than some processor cycles, assuming you don't pay for your connection on a per-minute or per-hour basis.
